Different anon. I like the idea, too. It's not entirely new. The thought of mixing DNA to create specialized creatures for corporate &/or government use is sort of the foundation of why genetic experimentation has been a sci fi/horror theme for decades. This literally goes back to the 1950s horror movie genre, and possibly further. The potential for abuse by bad actors is why there are real laws on the books in our real world in various countries to limit experimentation using human DNA.

Our classic cat waifur made from human & panther DNA:
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bagi,_the_Monster_of_Mighty_Nature

I wouldn't mind seeing a story or green on it here, but it would require an /hmofa/ spin rather than some horror/sc fi/conspiracy treatment à la /k/ meets /x/ and produces an abortion of a love child.
